<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6696] bin/solr start script should not enable autoSoftCommit by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6696</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting Solr with &lt;tt&gt;bin/solr&lt;/tt&gt; start script automatically sets this param &lt;tt&gt;-Dsolr.autoSoftCommit.maxTime=3000&lt;/tt&gt; without this being documented in help.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is really confusing, because when looking at solrconfig.xml, you expect the default to be disabled (&lt;tt&gt;-1&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think most of the JAVA OPTIONs being set in the script are sane, but I disagree with this one. The defaults for this script should be same as the defaults in the config. The user can always specify this as &lt;tt&gt;-a &quot;-Dsolr.autoSoftCommit.maxTime=NN&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
